description:
&lt;p&gt;The Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital Cytology department was been chosen in 2019 to be the provider of HPV primary testing for the East of England. This means that we are now testing up to 450,000 cervical screening samples per year for HPV using the high throughput Roche Cobas systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The laboratory also currently processes around 2,000 diagnostic cytology samples per year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a very busy department, and is sited in modern, well-equipped accommodation at the Cotman Centre, on Colney Lane.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Primary screening and rapid review of liquid based cervical cytology preparations and reporting of negative and inadequate samples.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clerical procedures associated with liquid based cervical cytology, to include sample registration, scanning of forms, entering own negative and inadequate reports on the database for routine cervical cytology and negative reports for Primary HPV screening.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting in the specimen reception - checking forms, retrieving and preparing vials for HPV testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting in the laboratory with routine technical procedures associated with liquid based cervical cytology including operation of the T5000/T2000 processor, staining and mounting as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participation in internal and external quality assessment including the National Health Service Cervical Screening Programme (NHSCSP) EQA scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the delivery of a high quality, safe and compassionate healthcare service, all staff are expected to act as a role model to others in all aspects of their work and consistently demonstrate NNUH’s ‘PRIDE’ values of People focused, Respect, Dedication, Integrity and Excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cytology department requires adequate staffing 9-5 plus a flexible approach to working outside normal hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time:&lt;/strong&gt; 20 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:&lt;/strong&gt; 15th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 3rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 29th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
